---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { ensureVisvambharaAccessSchema, hasApprovedAccess } from '@/lib/visvambhara-access';

const user = Astro.locals.user;
await ensureVisvambharaAccessSchema();
const approved = user ? await hasApprovedAccess(user.id) : false;
---
<BaseLayout title="Akasha-Q · QC³ for Viśvambhara · EduRankAI" description="Akasha-Q is the Quantum-Secure Command, Control & Communications backbone for the Viśvambhara autonomous swarm. Public preview; full briefing requires approved access.">

<style>
  body { background: #0a0a0c; color: #e8e8ee; }
  .aq-hero { padding: 60px 5vw 50px; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; }
  .aq-eyebrow { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; margin: 0; }
  .aq-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.04em; margin: 14px 0 18px; line-height: 0.96; max-width: 1000px; }
  .aq-title em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a78bfa, #67e8f9); -webkit-background-clip: text; background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; }
  .aq-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #9aa6b6; max-width: 740px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .aq-mission { padding: 0 5vw 40px; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .aq-pull { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(167,139,250,0.08), rgba(103,232,249,0.04)); border-left: 3px solid #a78bfa; padding: 24px 28px; border-radius: 0 14px 14px 0; }
  .aq-pull p { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.55; font-style: italic; color: #fff; margin: 0; }

  .aq-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 32px; padding: 24px 5vw; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; align-items: flex-start; border-top: 1px solid #1a1a25; }
  @media (max-width: 800px) { .aq-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 12px; } }
  .aq-label { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .aq-body { font-size: 15px; color: #cfd6da; line-height: 1.75; }
  .aq-body strong { color: #fff; }

  .aq-stages { padding: 40px 5vw; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .aq-stage-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
  .aq-stage { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 18px; }
  .aq-stage-n { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 28px; color: #a78bfa; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; }
  .aq-stage-t { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 18px; color: #fff; margin: 8px 0 6px; font-weight: 600; }
  .aq-stage-d { font-size: 12.5px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.5; }

  .aq-gate { padding: 48px 5vw 80px; max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .aq-gate-card { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #11131a, #1a1a25); border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 18px; padding: 36px; text-align: center; }
  .aq-gate-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fbbf24; font-weight: 700; }
  .aq-gate-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 36px; font-weight: 600; margin: 10px 0 12px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.1; }
  .aq-gate-sub { font-size: 15px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.65; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 24px; }
  .aq-gate-btn { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a78bfa, #67e8f9); color: #0a0a0c; padding: 14px 32px; border-radius: 10px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 800; display: inline-block; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }

  .aq-app-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; margin-top: 18px; }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .aq-app-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .aq-app { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px; }
  .aq-app-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fbbf24; font-weight: 700; }
  .aq-app-t { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 17px; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; margin: 4px 0 6px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .aq-app-d { font-size: 12.5px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.55; }
</style>

<main>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="aq-hero">
    <p class="aq-eyebrow">EduRankAI · Frontier research project</p>
    <h1 class="aq-title"><em>Akasha-Q</em>.<br/>The quantum-secure trust layer.</h1>
    <p class="aq-sub">QC³ — Quantum-Secure Command, Control & Communications — is what turns the Viśvambhara autonomous swarm from a research demonstrator into a system a Ministry of Defence can actually field. Entropy at the edge. Keys that survive a quantum adversary. Authenticated commands. Detection records signed into an unforgeable evidence ledger.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- MISSION CARD -->
  <section class="aq-mission">
    <div class="aq-pull">
      <p>We are not launching quantum satellites. We are building the quantum-secure trust layer — entropy, keys, and an unforgeable evidence chain — that turns Viśvambhara from an impressive demo into a system a Ministry of Defence can field. The Mother ship is our flight platform; sub-microradian pointing is our moat.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROW: positioning -->
  <section class="aq-row">
    <div>
      <p class="aq-label">Positioning</p>
    </div>
    <div class="aq-body">
      <p>Akasha-Q is <strong>not</strong> a parallel moonshot. It is the named QC³ subsystem of Viśvambhara — the part of the autonomous swarm programme that owns secure command, key distribution, time-of-flight, and the evidence chain. The Mother ship (VSP-M2) is simultaneously our HAPS relay, our orbital platform, and our flight subsystem testbed. One vehicle. One programme. Two synergistic value propositions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROW: 5 attack surfaces -->
  <section class="aq-row">
    <div>
      <p class="aq-label">Why C³ secures the whole swarm</p>
    </div>
    <div class="aq-body">
      <p>Five attack surfaces sit directly on Viśvambhara's stated value proposition:</p>
      <ol style="padding-left:20px;color:#cfd6da;line-height:1.85;font-size:14.5px;">
        <li><strong>Command injection / spoofing</strong> — a forged uplink could redirect the swarm, defeat hard-coded refusal classes. QKD/PQC-authenticated command channel mitigates.</li>
        <li><strong>Link jamming / denial of service</strong> — narrow-beam free-space optical (FSO) links are spatially hard to jam; verdict-only-upstream model minimises bandwidth dependence.</li>
        <li><strong>Interception of the intelligence picture</strong> — recorded today, decrypted later. QKD-derived keys are information-theoretically secure.</li>
        <li><strong>Harvest-now, decrypt-later on the evidence chain</strong> — PQC signatures (ML-DSA) anchored to QKD-distributed keys make the chain durable for decades.</li>
        <li><strong>Position & timing spoofing</strong> — quantum-authenticated timing relayed from the Mother; cross-checked against national satellite-navigation framework.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5 stages -->
  <section class="aq-stages">
    <p class="aq-label" style="margin-bottom:14px;">De-risked five-step progression</p>
    <div class="aq-stage-grid">
      <div class="aq-stage"><p class="aq-stage-n">01</p><p class="aq-stage-t">Terrestrial bench</p><p class="aq-stage-d">Optical bench BB84 + decoy-state at a partner photonics lab. Retire the QKD-protocol risk on the ground.</p></div>
      <div class="aq-stage"><p class="aq-stage-n">02</p><p class="aq-stage-t">UAV / HAPS relay</p><p class="aq-stage-d">Free-space optical link between two terminals at 20-30 km altitude. Retire atmospheric + atmospheric-pointing risk.</p></div>
      <div class="aq-stage"><p class="aq-stage-n">03</p><p class="aq-stage-t">CubeSat demonstrator</p><p class="aq-stage-d">Low-cost CubeSat with a single-photon detector + space-qualified optical bench. Retire the launch + space-qualified-optics risk.</p></div>
      <div class="aq-stage"><p class="aq-stage-n">04</p><p class="aq-stage-t">Operational LEO satellite</p><p class="aq-stage-d">First service-grade satellite delivering key material to ground stations. Integrated with the Viśvambhara Mother as the secondary platform.</p></div>
      <div class="aq-stage"><p class="aq-stage-n">05</p><p class="aq-stage-t">Constellation</p><p class="aq-stage-d">Continuous global key-distribution layer for the full Viśvambhara swarm.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Application wins (public preview) -->
  <section class="aq-row">
    <div>
      <p class="aq-label">Application wins</p>
    </div>
    <div class="aq-body">
      <p>Five contexts where the quantum layer is the difference between a demo and a deployable system:</p>
      <div class="aq-app-grid">
        <div class="aq-app"><p class="aq-app-eye">Win 01</p><p class="aq-app-t">Border-patrol swarm command</p><p class="aq-app-d">Forge-proof authenticated tasking; jam-resistant FSO uplink.</p></div>
        <div class="aq-app"><p class="aq-app-eye">Win 02</p><p class="aq-app-t">Evidence-grade detection chain</p><p class="aq-app-d">Court-admissible record durable against a future cryptographically-relevant quantum computer.</p></div>
        <div class="aq-app"><p class="aq-app-eye">Win 03</p><p class="aq-app-t">Disaster-zone GHQ link</p><p class="aq-app-d">A FSO uplink that does not depend on undamaged terrestrial fibre.</p></div>
        <div class="aq-app"><p class="aq-app-eye">Win 04</p><p class="aq-app-t">Strategic-asset key rotation</p><p class="aq-app-d">Long-lived material durable against harvest-now decrypt-later.</p></div>
        <div class="aq-app"><p class="aq-app-eye">Win 05</p><p class="aq-app-t">Central-bank settlement layer</p><p class="aq-app-d">Quantum-authenticated settlement messages with offline backstop.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gated section -->
  {!approved && (
    <section class="aq-gate">
      <div class="aq-gate-card">
        <p class="aq-gate-eye">Restricted briefing</p>
        <h2 class="aq-gate-title">Full execution blueprint requires <em style="color:#a78bfa;font-style:italic;">approved access</em>.</h2>
        <p class="aq-gate-sub">The detailed sections — corrected technical reality, optomechanical engineering moat, integration architecture, intellectual property strategy, corrected roadmap and budget, risk register, exit scenarios — are not part of the public preview. Apply for approved access if you have legitimate cause.</p>
        {user ? (
          <a href="/portal/visvambhara" class="aq-gate-btn">Request access →</a>
        ) : (
          <a href="/portal/login?next=/products/akasha-q" class="aq-gate-btn">Sign in to apply →</a>
        )}
      </div>
    </section>
  )}

  {approved && (
    <section class="aq-row">
      <div>
        <p class="aq-label" style="color:#86efac;">Approved · Full briefing</p>
      </div>
      <div class="aq-body">
        <p><strong>Strategic repositioning (full).</strong> The standalone framing fails because: customers buy track record; incumbents have effectively unlimited runway; sales cycle measured in years; QKD is not universally better than software-only post-quantum cryptography. As a parallel moonshot, Akasha-Q is fragile on all four axes. Folded into Viśvambhara, it becomes essential infrastructure with a captive first customer.</p>
        <p><strong>The real bottleneck</strong> is optomechanical engineering, not quantum physics. The quantum protocols (BB84, decoy-state, BBM92) are textbook and largely de-risked nationally. What stops quantum start-ups for years is space-qualified optical payload engineering: sub-microradian acquisition, tracking and pointing across a target moving at 7.6 km/s; an optical bench that holds sub-micron alignment through orbital thermal cycling; single-photon detectors that survive radiation; and a payload that survives launch and then re-aligns itself in orbit.</p>
        <p><strong>Integration architecture.</strong> Akasha-Q is a Mother-ship subsystem. The QC³ payload shares its mechanical bus, thermal management, and power budget with the Mother flight platform. Co-developing the quantum terminal collapses two of the most expensive rungs (HAPS relay + orbital demonstrator) into an aerospace programme that exists anyway — no separate bus, no separate launch contract, no separate platform team.</p>
        <p><strong>Roadmap, budget & team.</strong> Hire optomechanical engineering and pointing-systems leads first; quantum specialists second. Stage-gated capital deployment per the five-step ladder, with each stage retiring a specific risk for the next. Budget weight on the optical bench + ATP, not on quantum protocol R&D.</p>
        <p style="color:#9aa6b6;font-size:13px;font-style:italic;">Full version 2.0 blueprint — appendices, glossary, precedent missions, QKD-vs-PQC decision tree — available via secure document portal. Contact the founding team.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  )}

</main>
</BaseLayout>
